Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.13,0:00:03.60,Default,Girl1,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear about Ayano?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.60,0:00:07.01,Default,Girl2,0000,0000,0000,,She was trying to escape, wasn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.01,0:00:07.86,Default,Girl1,0000,0000,0000,,I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.26,0:00:10.47,Default,Girl3,0000,0000,0000,,You think she died because \Nshe tried to get away?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.47,0:00:11.68,Default,Girl1,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.85,0:00:16.57,Default,Girl2,0000,0000,0000,,Ogura's brother died \Nthat same day, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.89,0:00:17.65,Default,Girl1,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.65,0:00:19.57,Default,Girl3,0000,0000,0000,,Hadn't he shut himself up at home?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.57,0:00:20.20,Default,Girl2,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.74,0:00:23.97,Default,Girl1,0000,0000,0000,,You know, I heard something \Nabout the class trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.97,0:00:26.11,Default,Girl1,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, it does have significance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.11,0:00:27.25,Default,Girl2,0000,0000,0000,,Significance?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.25,0:00:29.59,Default,Girl3,0000,0000,0000,,You mean, asking the gods for help?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.00,0:00:32.42,Default,Girl1,0000,0000,0000,,I heard the class was \Nsaved once by doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.67,0:02:05.60,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Stupid...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.08,0:02:08.52,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Stupid brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.55,0:02:11.63,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.29,0:02:15.26,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.22,0:02:18.70,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry! Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.14,0:02:27.24,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.78,0:02:32.50,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you. \NI'm Kouichi Sakakibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.91,0:02:56.92,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Sakitani Memorial Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.28,0:02:51.45,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Got the tape?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.45,0:02:52.84,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.84,0:02:53.80,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.80,0:02:54.89,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.89,0:02:56.92,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid to listen to it alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.43,0:03:12.12,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Let's take a picture to \Ncommemorate this occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.52,0:03:14.75,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,It's our last summer break \Nin junior high, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.08,0:03:15.88,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.03,0:03:19.90,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Sakitani Memorial Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.39,0:03:19.88,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone line up over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.81,0:03:24.89,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.89,0:03:26.76,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get the teachers in the shot, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.41,0:03:31.24,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, almost ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.04,0:03:35.23,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Sakakibara and Misaki, squeeze \Na little closer together.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.49,0:03:44.57,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,You should get to be in one, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.57,0:03:45.82,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.11,0:03:48.45,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Here goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.62,0:03:52.64,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Mochizuki, you and \NMs. Mikami are too far apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.64,0:03:54.24,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Same goes for Sakaki and Misaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.86,0:03:56.66,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Kazami, you're fine there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.36,0:03:59.96,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,All right, say "cheese!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.48,0:04:08.38,Default,Mikami,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow, we'll visit the shrine \Nto pray for our safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.38,0:04:09.31,Default,All,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.32,0:04:11.93,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,This is a nice lodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.71,0:04:16.61,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,A local business donated its recreation center.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.09,0:04:21.16,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,It seems a bit extravagant for \Na school group, if you ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.16,0:04:23.64,Default,Numata,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.64,0:04:26.20,Default,Numata,0000,0000,0000,,We've kept all the rooms open for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.55,0:04:29.41,Default,Mikami,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for having us \Nfor the next three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.41,0:04:31.08,Default,Numata,0000,0000,0000,,We're happy to. Thanks for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.36,0:04:34.30,Default,Numata,0000,0000,0000,,If there's anything you need, \Ndon't hesitate to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.64,0:04:41.72,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.18,0:04:44.56,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,I'm playing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.60,0:04:55.24,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now, this is the important part.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.66,0:04:58.25,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Right after we finally reached \Nthe bottom of the mountain,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.25,0:05:00.00,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}that's when it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.00,0:05:03.16,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And by {\i0}it{\i1}, I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.02,0:05:04.95,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.42,0:05:08.92,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It happened in the forest, \Noutside the lodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.92,0:05:12.54,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I got into an argument \Nwith a guy named [*].
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.54,0:05:16.10,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We ended up trading blows.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.10,0:05:18.54,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And then... And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.10,0:05:23.05,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The next thing I knew, he wasn't moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.51,0:05:26.47,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He was lying under a huge tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.26,0:05:30.95,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When I looked closer, \NI saw he'd been impaled on a branch.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.61,0:05:34.48,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He was dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.70,0:05:39.03,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Terrified, I ran back to \Nmy room at the lodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.73,0:05:43.61,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It had been decided that \Nwe'd be staying an extra night.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.61,0:05:46.62,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The police came to see us about \Nthe lightning and the fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.62,0:05:49.10,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They asked me a lot of questions,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.10,0:05:52.50,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but I couldn't tell \Nthem anything about [*].
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.76,0:05:56.12,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I hardly slept at all that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.48,0:06:02.06,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was sure someone would find \N[*]'s body and everyone would freak.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.99,0:06:07.38,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But in the morning, there were \Nno signs of that happening,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.64,0:06:12.44,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}so I went back into the \Nforest to find it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.44,0:06:15.69,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But... it wasn't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.69,0:06:19.22,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It had vanished without a trace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.77,0:06:22.18,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was so bewildered...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.56,0:06:26.79,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I asked the others what \Nhad happened to [*].
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.19,0:06:29.95,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But they all just looked \Nat me like I was crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.25,0:06:34.78,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"Who's that? I don't know \Nanyone with that name."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.57,0:06:40.78,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They even said there were 19 \Nstudents on the trip, not 20.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.80,0:06:44.84,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's when it dawned on me...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.28,0:06:53.62,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The guy I'd killed must have been \Nthe extra student all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.77,0:06:58.27,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I know without a doubt that I killed [*].
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.06,0:07:00.76,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Nothing will change that fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.19,0:07:04.52,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's why I decided \Nto come clean here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.18,0:07:07.73,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is my confession.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.77,0:07:10.70,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's been two weeks since the trip,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.70,0:07:15.29,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and only I, the sole person deeply involved in his death, still remember [*].
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.88,0:07:19.33,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I get the feeling it's \Nonly a matter of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.81,0:07:23.15,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's why, while my memory is still clear,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.15,0:07:24.71,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to tell you the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.00,0:07:28.75,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and how to stop the calamity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.86,0:07:30.76,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Are you listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.18,0:07:32.99,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Send them back to death, \Nwhere they belong.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.75,0:07:35.65,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Send the dead back to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.58,0:07:40.80,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's how to stop the \Ncalamity once it's begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.59,0:07:52.24,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,We couldn't hear his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.78,0:07:56.62,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean this has been altered?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.10,0:07:57.98,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.01,0:08:01.37,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Then, it must be real.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.87,0:08:05.00,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,There'd be no reason to alter a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.79,0:08:11.86,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we don't need the name.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.31,0:08:13.97,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,What matters is how \Nto stop the calamity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.32,0:08:17.87,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,They say there's no way to \Ntell the dead from the living.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.67,0:08:20.72,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,And they don't know they're dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.72,0:08:23.04,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Is there any way to tell at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.04,0:08:24.75,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,There doesn't seem to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.75,0:08:27.61,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Matsunaga's case was pure coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.80,0:08:34.49,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,You don't suppose the extra \Nstudent is here, at this lodge, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.04,0:08:42.86,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Say we do figure out who it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.41,0:08:45.13,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Then what?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.55,0:08:47.96,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Are we supposed to... kill them?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.18,0:08:49.09,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Well—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.09,0:08:51.71,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Could you kill a classmate?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.80,0:09:13.33,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,You know, I've been thinking \Nabout who the extra could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.95,0:09:15.49,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have someone in mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.49,0:09:16.53,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.53,0:09:24.12,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,I just think there must be \Nsome way to tell who it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.14,0:09:26.89,Default,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Keep inhaler in bag when not in use.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.63,0:09:27.31,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe there is, and we \Njust don't know it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.70,0:09:28.69,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.61,0:09:34.57,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,May I have a moment, Ms. Mikami?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.38,0:09:39.43,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Since we're all together, \Nthere's something I'd like to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.75,0:09:40.96,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.91,0:09:43.93,Default,Mikami,0000,0000,0000,,Um, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.93,0:09:45.73,Default,Mikami,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead, Akazawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.26,0:09:56.38,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Since May, we have experienced \Nnothing but misfortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.38,0:10:00.27,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Just last month, even \NMr. Kubodera became a victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.17,0:10:03.43,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,To begin, I'd like to apologize for my
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.43,0:10:06.16,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,great ineptitude as the \Nhead of countermeasures.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.46,0:10:10.70,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, though it remains unclear
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.70,0:10:14.33,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,whether this trip will lead \Nus toward a resolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.09,0:10:19.98,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I sincerely believe that you, \NMisaki, bear some degree
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.98,0:10:22.43,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,of responsibility for the \Ndisasters we've faced.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.41,0:10:25.22,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Why...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.00,0:10:31.85,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,If Misaki had properly upheld her \Nrole as the nonexistent student,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.85,0:10:33.48,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I believe no one would've died.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.81,0:10:35.01,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.40,0:10:37.45,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,What happened was unavoidable.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.45,0:10:38.99,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,She couldn't help how it all went down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.99,0:10:40.13,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Really, now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.50,0:10:46.05,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,If she had been completely thorough \Nin avoiding contact with Sakakibara,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.05,0:10:47.62,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,the countermeasure would have succeeded.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.62,0:10:48.05,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,But—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.05,0:10:52.16,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I believe the primary person responsible \Nfor its failure is Misaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.16,0:10:52.84,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.78,0:10:55.59,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,What do you expect \Nher to do about it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.85,0:11:00.72,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.25,0:11:05.22,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,We have yet to hear one word \Nof apology from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.80,0:11:09.60,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, Misaki, the moment you \Nwere allowed to exist again,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.60,0:11:11.37,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,you carried on as if nothing happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.93,0:11:13.23,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,There's no point.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.82,0:11:17.73,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Would apologizing serve any purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.56,0:11:19.95,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,If it will, I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.33,0:11:29.41,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Misaki, you have nothing to apologize for.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.35,0:11:33.54,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.99,0:11:35.00,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It's my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.00,0:11:35.84,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,It's not!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.84,0:11:36.50,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.46,0:11:38.66,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,This is pointless!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.66,0:11:41.84,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,What's important is figuring \Nout who the extra—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.84,0:11:43.90,Default,Kazami,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Wakui, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.34,0:11:50.48,Default,Maejima,0000,0000,0000,,Are you in pain?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.48,0:11:51.59,Default,Kazami,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.94,0:11:55.65,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Is this boy asthmatic?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.65,0:11:58.12,Default,Kazami,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He always has this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.12,0:12:02.23,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,An inhaler? Shouldn't he use this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.78,0:12:04.04,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,It's empty?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.04,0:12:04.99,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a spare?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.82,0:12:11.56,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Call an ambulance! \NMs. Mikami, call an ambulance now!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.56,0:12:12.08,Default,Numata,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.55,0:12:16.42,Default,Numata,0000,0000,0000,,Our phones haven't been working since \Nyesterday. We can't make calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.42,0:12:18.00,Default,Numata,0000,0000,0000,,We've arranged for repairs...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.71,0:12:18.00,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,It's out of range.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.38,0:12:19.76,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Does anyone have service?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.00,0:12:22.03,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Call 119! Get an ambulance here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.56,0:12:24.62,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,It says there's an antenna here, \Nbut I can't connect!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.62,0:12:26.01,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Mine won't work, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.01,0:12:27.26,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,There's no service.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.97,0:12:30.02,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,I'll drive him to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.42,0:12:50.74,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.08,0:12:55.29,Default,Mikami,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not the one you should be worried about.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.84,0:12:59.00,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we shouldn't go up \Nthe mountain tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.63,0:13:01.32,Default,Mikami,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe not.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.76,0:13:08.20,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Sakakibara...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.12,0:13:09.95,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.43,0:13:12.07,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.07,0:13:13.20,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.20,0:13:16.15,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,You stood up for me in the dining room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.33,0:13:19.02,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that. It was nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.67,0:13:21.14,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,And it wasn't just me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.56,0:13:23.82,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,There was Mochizuki and Teshigawara, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.82,0:13:24.76,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.59,0:13:30.33,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Will you come see me later?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.59,0:13:34.83,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I have my own room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.30,0:13:36.40,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.17,0:13:39.24,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I want to see the photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.81,0:13:42.48,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Where was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.92,0:13:44.70,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,In a detached room at our house.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.70,0:13:46.53,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,My grandma found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.34,0:13:50.02,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know why it \Nwas in there, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.72,0:13:51.64,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.08,0:13:56.06,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,My aunt Reiko uses that room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.46,0:13:58.08,Default,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}With everyone in grade 9, class 3\NMarch 16, 1973
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.32,0:14:08.21,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Can you tell which one \NMisaki Yomiyama is?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.72,0:14:13.87,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I can see that one \Nperson looks strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.34,0:14:17.31,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Strange? In what way?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.60,0:14:18.87,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Like...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.08,0:14:23.72,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,He's kind of blurry, compared \Nto the others in the photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.72,0:14:25.35,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Distorted, somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.35,0:14:26.43,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.43,0:14:29.71,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,What about the color? \NDo you see any strange colors?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.29,0:14:32.30,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,No, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.07,0:14:34.26,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.28,0:14:37.49,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Are these other photos your mom's, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.49,0:14:38.33,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.09,0:14:40.91,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,They really did look alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.45,0:14:42.65,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.65,0:14:46.27,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Your mother and your aunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.78,0:14:48.15,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.15,0:14:50.33,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Their faces looked the same as kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.25,0:14:55.79,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Does Reiko do painting at home?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.79,0:14:56.79,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.79,0:15:00.43,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,She considers that her real job.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.96,0:15:01.97,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.78,0:15:06.76,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You were drawing something, \Ntoo, weren't you? An angel?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.76,0:15:09.37,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Who was the model for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.37,0:15:10.58,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It was...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.59,0:15:14.02,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Your cousin Misaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.47,0:15:15.94,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.81,0:15:20.06,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,When we first met, at the hospital,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.71,0:15:26.48,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,were you taking that doll \Nto your cousin, after she passed away?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.48,0:15:28.31,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find that strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.88,0:15:30.00,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.00,0:15:32.54,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It's sort of complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.09,0:15:36.45,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I don't usually like talking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.86,0:15:38.97,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Could you tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.43,0:15:40.23,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.57,0:15:45.38,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,My mother Kirika's real name is Yukiyo,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.88,0:15:49.04,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,and Misaki's mother's name is Mitsuyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.04,0:15:52.18,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,They're twins, almost identical.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.61,0:15:56.21,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,When they grew up, \Nthey both got married,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.21,0:15:58.35,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,and Mitsuyo became a mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.94,0:16:00.95,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,To your cousin Misaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.95,0:16:03.36,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,And one other.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.27,0:16:06.22,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,She had twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.69,0:16:07.71,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.71,0:16:11.31,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,One year later, Yukiyo \Nbecame pregnant, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.76,0:16:15.49,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,But her baby never came into this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.49,0:16:16.85,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You mentioned that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.85,0:16:21.34,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Yukiyo was so grief-stricken, \Nshe nearly had a breakdown.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.45,0:16:25.18,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,To make matters worse, \Nthe Fujioka household,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.18,0:16:27.00,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,into which the twins were born, \Nwas in financial trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.72,0:16:29.90,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,The Misaki household, on the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.90,0:16:32.78,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,needed something to soothe Yukiyo's heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.19,0:16:36.49,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It was a matter of supply and demand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.49,0:16:37.39,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You mean—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.39,0:16:39.26,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I was given to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.45,0:16:43.97,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I think they gave me to her, instead of Misaki,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.46,0:16:46.83,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,because of my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.83,0:16:48.00,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.52,0:16:52.23,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,If the Misakis took \Nin a daughter named Misaki,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.23,0:16:53.94,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,her name would be Misaki Misaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.34,0:17:00.56,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I've been raised as Yukiyo's, as Kirika's only daughter, for as long as I can remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.22,0:17:04.67,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I think I was in 5th grade \Nwhen I discovered the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.13,0:17:07.79,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,My grandmother accidentally let it slip.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.79,0:17:10.74,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen my mother so flustered.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.07,0:17:14.43,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,She was probably planning to \Nkeep it a secret my whole life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.33,0:17:18.24,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,What happened once you knew the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.87,0:17:23.91,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to meet Mitsuyo \NFujioka, my other mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.91,0:17:27.10,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,and I told Kirika that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.10,0:17:30.83,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,At first, she looked incredibly sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.08,0:17:34.50,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,But then she was furious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.50,0:17:37.30,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,She didn't want you to \Nmeet your birth mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.67,0:17:38.69,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I guess not.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.62,0:17:41.75,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,She doesn't interfere in my life much,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.75,0:17:44.30,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,except, as I've mentioned, for certain things.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.30,0:17:45.76,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Right, I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.11,0:17:49.21,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I think she feels anxious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.70,0:17:54.34,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably why she makes \Nme carry a cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.09,0:17:58.03,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,But while all that was going on,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.03,0:18:00.10,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I was secretly meeting with Misaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.77,0:18:05.50,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,By then, she also knew \Nthat we were twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.50,0:18:09.41,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,We felt that we were connected, \Nwhether we wanted to be or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.12,0:18:13.25,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,She often sneaked over to my house.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.62,0:18:17.68,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,She said she liked my house because \Nit was full of pretty dolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.39,0:18:23.04,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,When I asked her what she \Nwanted for her birthday in April,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.04,0:18:25.87,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,she said, "I want that doll."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.29,0:18:30.01,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,But soon after starting \N9th grade, she suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.61,0:18:32.25,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,That's what you were doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.69,0:18:35.16,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I had made a promise to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.59,0:18:40.07,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,So you were sisters, not cousins...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.53,0:18:41.26,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.76,0:18:44.89,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you told me \N"it may have already begun."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.55,0:18:47.25,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,So you remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.74,0:18:48.46,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.12,0:18:52.13,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you tell me that day?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.99,0:18:54.14,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.16,0:18:56.36,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.23,0:18:59.00,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want to believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.66,0:19:02.99,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want to believe Misaki had died
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.99,0:19:05.12,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,because of some crazy curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.42,0:19:06.37,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.26,0:19:09.25,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I could only call her my cousin.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.61,0:19:11.10,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want to say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.60,0:19:18.96,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,The Misaki who died in April \Nwas the first victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.40,0:19:21.39,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,If that's true, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.70,0:19:27.59,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone else seems to think the \Ncalamity began in May, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.59,0:19:29.64,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,The extra student was already
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.64,0:19:32.79,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,in the class before I came to Yomi North.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.83,0:19:39.09,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Is that why you're so \Ncertain that I'm not dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.51,0:19:40.24,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.47,0:19:43.97,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Because I wasn't in the \Nclass back in April?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.97,0:19:47.16,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,There's that, but it's not the main reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.34,0:19:50.18,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,What's your main reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.04,0:19:52.11,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It's...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.46,0:19:58.56,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,This eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.84,0:20:04.41,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,This doll's eye tells me you're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.76,0:20:05.93,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Your left eye?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.36,0:20:07.90,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I think I told you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.90,0:20:10.43,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,that it lets me see things \Nthat should remain unseen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.72,0:20:13.26,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. What can it see?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.83,0:20:14.94,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,The...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.24,0:20:18.78,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,...color of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.24,0:20:21.56,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,The color of things close to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.56,0:20:22.40,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Color?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.94,0:20:24.27,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,What color is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.30,0:20:32.15,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,A color I've never seen \Nwith my right eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.15,0:20:35.77,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't belong with \Ncolors like red and blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.52,0:20:38.34,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It's unique.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.69,0:20:43.47,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,And you can only see that \Ncolor in people who are dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.47,0:20:45.39,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It's clearest in dead people,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.09,0:20:48.98,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,and faint in those with \Nserious illnesses or injuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.58,0:20:53.31,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You mean, you can tell when \Npeople are about to die?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.06,0:20:58.10,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,You can't understand how I \Ncan see these things, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.76,0:21:00.08,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.08,0:21:02.83,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I've had to accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.45,0:21:07.76,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I've never even talked \Nto Misaki about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.34,0:21:10.37,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,At some point,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.37,0:21:13.40,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I decided to keep this eye \Ncovered for the rest of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.76,0:21:21.76,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I wanted to see \Nthat photo from 26 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.18,0:21:26.91,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You could see the color of \Ndeath in Misaki Yomiyama?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.91,0:21:27.90,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.69,0:21:32.74,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It's the first time I've ever seen \Nthat color so clearly in a photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.09,0:21:38.95,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see the color of death in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.45,0:21:42.15,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,That's how I know it's not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.63,0:21:43.99,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,You're not the extra.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.42,0:21:48.24,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,And you know it's not you \Nfor the same reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.80,0:21:55.37,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean you already \Nknow who the extra person is?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.85,0:22:03.09,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I try to keep my eyepatch on at school.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.90,0:22:07.30,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,But you wrote "Who is dead?" on your desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.82,0:22:10.97,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't as if my finding \Nout would change anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.24,0:22:15.30,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I did wonder, though... So...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.37,0:22:18.19,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,What about now?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.59,0:22:24.32,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Is the dead person here on this trip?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.30,0:22:33.58,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,The extra person...
